-- India Company Profit Estimates for Quarter to Sept. 30
-- B y   P a r e s h   J a t a k i a
-- 2010-11-15T07:09:26Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-22/india-company-profit-estimates-for-quarter-to-sept-30-table-.html
The following are the mean of analysts’ forecasts
for profit and sales compiled by Bloomberg for the  30 companies  in the benchmark
Bombay Stock Exchange  Sensitive Index  for the quarter ended Sept. 30. Total
profit reported was 0.3 percent above analysts’ estimates and 7.6 percent higher
from a year earlier period.  Company names are in alphabetical order and figures are in billions of
rupees (1 billion rupees = $22.2 million). The estimates are based on figures
submitted by analysts. Actual profit and sales declared in the quarter is shown
in the middle column. Company tickers and time periods are listed in brackets.  Note: * For banks, the estimates refer to net interest income.  # includes one-time gain/loss.  ^ Group numbers not included in total.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 Paresh Jatakia  in Mumbai at 
